1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,610
Some of the most practical success-building wisdom is found in that biblical quotation stating that faith can move mountains.

2
00:00:09,201 --> 00:00:13,731
Believe, really believe you can move a mountain, and you can.

3
00:00:14,161 --> 00:00:20,931
Not many people believe that they can move mountains, so, as a result, not many people do.

4
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:30,131
On some occasion, you've probably heard someone say something like, it's nonsense to think you can make a mountain move away just by saying,

5
00:00:30,161 --> 00:00:31,651
mountain, move away.

6
00:00:31,761 --> 00:00:33,491
It's simply impossible.

7
00:00:34,081 --> 00:00:38,851
People who think this way have belief confused with wishful thinking.

8
00:00:39,121 --> 00:00:42,530
And true enough, you can't wish away a mountain.

9
00:00:42,721 --> 00:00:46,131
You can't wish yourself into an executive suite.

10
00:00:46,401 --> 00:00:52,371
Nor can you wish yourself into a five-bedroom, three-bath house or the high-income brackets.

11
00:00:52,721 --> 00:00:56,291
You can't wish yourself into a position of leadership.

12
00:00:56,721 --> 00:00:59,571
But you can move a mountain with belief.

13
00:00:59,841 --> 00:01:04,050
You can win success by believing you can succeed.

14
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:08,851
There is nothing magical or mystical about the power of belief.

15
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,411
Belief works this way.

16
00:01:11,761 --> 00:01:19,971
Belief, the I'm positive I can attitude, generates the power, skill, and energy needed to do.

17
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:24,531
When you believe I can do it, the how to do it develops.

18
00:01:25,201 --> 00:01:29,811
Every day, all over the nation, young people start working in new jobs.

19
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:36,131
Each of them wishes that someday he could enjoy the success that goes with reaching the top.

20
00:01:36,481 --> 00:01:43,091
But the majority of these young people simply don't have the belief that it takes to reach the top rungs.

21
00:01:43,201 --> 00:01:45,091
And they don't reach the top.

22
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:51,811
Believing it's impossible to climb high, they do not discover the steps that lead to great heights.

23
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,490
Their behavior remains that of the average person.

24
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,531
But a small number of these young people really believe they will succeed.

25
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:04,851
They approach their work with the I'm-going-to-the-top attitude,

26
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:07,971
and with substantial belief they reach the top.

